# Persona Studio — security rules

- **Never give an agent production DB credentials, unscoped infra tokens, or
  production deletion access.** Work against local/seed/non-production data.
- No secrets in source control; validate env with `validation/env.ts`.
- Keep three identities separate: fictional persona, real participant, anonymous
  reference. Real participant names never appear on persona-facing screens by
  default.
- Apply the correct `ConfidentialityLabel` to sources. Minimise personal data.
- Never run destructive database operations or edit production data.

See `docs/persona-studio/SECURITY.md`.
